content:
I see the issue clearly from your screenshot:

### ⚠️ **The remote URL currently configured is:**
```
origin git@github.com;palios-taey/palios-taey-nova.git (fetch)
origin git@github.com;palios-taey/palios-taey-nova.git (push)
```

Notice the typo: you're using a **semicolon `;`** after `github.com` instead of a colon `:`.

---

### ✅ **How to fix this:**

Run this exact command to correct the remote URL:
```bash
git remote set-url origin git@github.com:palios-taey/palios-taey-nova.git
```

Then verify it was correctly set:
```bash
git remote -v
```

You should see:
```
origin git@github.com:palios-taey/palios-taey-nova.git (fetch)
origin git@github.com:palios-taey/palios-taey-nova.git (push)
```

Now, re-run the push:
```bash
git push origin main --force
```

This will resolve the issue completely!
